The Agile Test Quadrant is a model that categorizes tests based on:

Business-facing vs Technology-facing

Supporting the team vs Critiquing the product

It helps Agile teams decide what type of tests to perform and when.

Agile Test Quadrant Overview
Quadrant	                          Focus	                                         Type                                     Examples
Q1	                           Technology-facing	                          Supporting the team	                  Unit tests,component tests
Q2	                           Business-facing	                            Supporting the team	                  Functional testing,acceptance tests,BDD
Q3	                           Business-facing	                            Critiquing the product	              Exploratory testing,usability testing
Q4	                           Technology-facing	                          Critiquing the product	              Performance,security,load testing
Experience-Based Testing & Agile Test Quadrant
What Is Experience-Based Testing?

Experience-Based Testing relies on:

Testerâ€™s domain knowledge

Intuition

Past defect experience

Examples:

Exploratory Testing

Error Guessing

Checklist-based Testing

Which Quadrant Is Used for Experience-Based Testing?

Quadrant 3 (Q3)

Why Quadrant 3?
1. Focus on Critiquing the Product

Q3 is about evaluating the product from a user perspective.

Experience-based testing finds issues that scripted tests may miss.

2. Business-Facing Tests

Experience-based testing checks:

Usability

User workflows

Real-world scenarios

These align with business expectations.

3. Human-Centered Testing

Requires creativity,intuition and tester expertise.

Cannot be fully automated.

Examples of Q3 Experience-Based Testing:

Exploratory testing

Usability testing

User journey testing

UAT support

Edge-case discovery based on experience
